    are @{"Copyright" link "AFD-Copyright/main" 28} © @{" Ralf Heinert " link "Author"} 1998,
    all rights reserved.

    It underlies the conditions which are described in the
    "Standard Amiga FD-Software Copyright Note".
    It is distributed as @{b}Giftware@{ub} as defined in @{b}chapter 4@{ub}
    (Please don't send sweets, though)
    For more information please read the @{" AFD Copyright " link "AFD-Copyright/main"} (V 1.2)

    This guide links directly into the mentioned text and expands some of its points.

    1.@{" Copyright " link "AFD-Copyright/main" 28}

    With the following adaption:
    You may edit the script if you like, although on your own risk.
    If you intend to do so, please keep a unmodified backup copy of the original package.
    Only this completely unchanged original copy of the package with exactly this @{"contents" link /FileTypeUtils.contents/main}
    may bredistributed, but not any scripts you modified yourself.

    2.@{" Distribution " link "AFD-Copyright/main" 42}

    With regards to chapter 2a, see my remarks about chapter one.

    3.@{" Disclaimer " link "AFD-Copyright/main" 60}

    In a nutshell, this means:
    This software is provided to you "as is". No warranty, neither
    explicitely nor implicitely, is made.
    The author can not be hold responsible for direct, indirect,
    incidental or accidental damage or loss of data which may
    be caused by using this program. The user uses this software
    entirely on his own risk, especially if you decide to change
    any script of software package.

    4.@{" Return Service " link "AFD-Copyright/main" 76}

    With the following specification:
    4.g. @{b}Giftware@{ub} - You are expected to send me a GIFT.
         For example:
         - a copy of your self written ARexx-script (TritionRexx, MuiRexx) or
         - some money or
         - a Amiga 6000-060 PowerPC-Tower ;-)



    Geez, the concept of AFD sure has still some room for improvements ...




